        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         You should have Invoke Fear (Fear upgrade) by now I think. </P><P>Fear kiting is when you slow a MOB (darkness), fear it, and then send pet, DOT, DD etc until it's dead.  Of course the idea is that you are relatively safe since the MOB is feared, and with DOTs eating away at it and your pet beating on it's back it won't last long.</P><P>There's also aggro kiting FYI.  Aggro kiting is when you slow a MOB (darkness), gain it's aggro by casting some nasty spell on it (usually a DOT), sending pet and then taking off running.  The MOB will lumber slowly behind you with DOTs eating away at it and your pet beating on it's back.</P><P>There are variations depending on the situation and you don't always have to use a pet.</P><P>Hope that helps.</P><P>Insert witty comment and original artwork here.</P><P>Corto Muerte<BR>42 Gnecromancer<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
