        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         The other thing I would add is that as you gain in levels, don't automatically switch to your upper level spells.  (referring to status changes like darkness, fears, roots, etc)  When you get new status upgrades, try them out in comparison to your old spells and factor in the new mana costs.</P><P>I'm still using the level 34 root most of the time at level 60 for example.</P><P>It does not have a delay on the spell refreshing, and its CHEAP.  With roots the big important thing is maximum duration, mana cost, cast time, and refresh time.  34 root owns in almost every category except for the maximum duration of course.  But roots can break randomlly at any tick, so in a lot of ways, its better.</P><P>Spook the dead?  Lovely spell.</P><P>Whenever I find myself using fear with undead, this spell is supreme.  The undead fears are much cheaper in mana cost then the regular fears, and seem to be more effective to me.</P><P>Level 4 fear?  Yup, frequently memmed.  </P><P></P><P><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=107355" target="_blank">Those who have turned away, shall be turned upon. <br> Lich Ravanta Suffer</a>  <img src=icon_smile_evil.gif border=0 align=middle><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
