        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=33093&amp;TOPIC_ID=4231&amp;FORUM_ID=13&amp;CAT_ID=2&amp;Forum_Title=Newbie+Land&amp;Topic_Title=Fear+Kiting&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Main thing to remeber about fear kiting is that some mobs will assist, and while the mob is feared, it is going to go, where it is going to go. if thier is a huge pile of mobs where it feels like running to, well it is time to whip out FD and let bones take one for the team.  your only other option is to root the mob, but if root wears off before fear, ol MR. Nasty is going to head back to his party of pals. Also, if you are going to use root in that situation, be sure to spam hit your /pet back off hot key.  pets tend to break root rather quick, and can get eaten by mobs if they don't break it.<BR>As you fear kite more, you will notice that mobs always run the same direction from the same area (pathing), get used to where they run, and find places where you can safly fear kite mobs, with few to no adds.</P><P>Fear kiting can be fun and quite rewarding, as fear tends not to use alot of mana. and if you run out, you can let your pet do the rest of the work.  If you run out of mana on one mob, chances are your pet is not going to get it's attention from you even if fear breaks, so you can just lead it arround while your pet takes him out.  if you pet is low on health, and the mob tunrs on him. get a bit of distance and sit down.  usualy works to make mobs want to make you into a breakfast cerial more than ol jaboner.</P><P>also dooming darkness is the one most necros use for fear kiting.  at 55, when I fear kite, it is still the one I cast.</P><P>It cost less mana, and cast quicker than cascading dark.  which, since when fear kiting I usualy have my pet to do most of the dmg, I do not need the extra damage. but a spell you can get to max casting range, stop, and cast before the mob hits you, if it was resisted the first time is a life saver.  for really fast mobs, I will some times mem and even lower level fear for that reason.  just need to get them moving away from me, then I can burn mana on resited darknesses =)</P><P>Of course all that I have said here, you will learn . . . the hard way . . . we all do sooner of later.</P><P><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11832" target="_blank">Bringer of Darkness</a><BR><a href="http://members.cox.net/umbrae/pic.jpg" target="_blank">Signature Pic PG</a><BR><a href="http://members.cox.net/umbrae/topless.jpg" target="_blank">Signature Pic R</a></center><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
