        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I'm a L40 Erudite Necro on Zebuxoruk. I've just recently gotten back into soloing with my 39 pet (24-39 seemed harder for some reason). As sick as I am of The Overthere, I'm still making really good progress toward 44 hunting everything but Tigers. Here's my normal method for dark blues:<BR><h3>Preparation:</h3><ul><li>Greater Shielding</li><li>Spirit Armor</li><li>Steel Like Skin</li><li>Spirit Armor Pet</li><li>Jboot (SOW if you don't have Jboots). SOW makes all the difference.</li></ul><BR><h3>Just before pull:</h3><ul><li>Augment Death on Pet if needed.</li></ul><BR><h3>The Pull</h3><ul><li>Pull at maximum range with Dooming Darkness.</li></ul><BR><h4>If Darkness sticks on first try</h4><ul><li>Fear</li><li>Send in Pet</li><li>Venom of the Snake</li><li>Sit</li><li>CoB/Tap if needed.</li></ul><BR><h4>If Darkness fails:</h4><ul><li>Send in pet</li><li>Invoke Fear</li><li>Dooming Darkness until it sticks</li><li>Venom of the Snake</li><li>CoB if under 3 bubs of mana</li><li>Sit and Tap as needed.</li></ul></P><P>Before the June 6 patch, I'd Dark, Fear, Dot and wait until damage was almost at half before sending in the pet. Now that pets don't take experience, you can send it in a lot earlier and that helps a lot!</P><P>Now I'm about as cowardly a necro as you'll find. My philosophy is "He who fights and runs away lives to fight another day (and doesn't have to make a naked corpse run)." Having said that, I'm now pretty comfortable pulling with as little as two bubs of HP as long as I have full mana and am reasonably close to either a zone or a guard. Mana is more important than health at this point. I start tapping when I'm at half HP generally.</P><P>When things are going well, I typically have only used 2-3 bubs of mana and have 4 bubs of health when the mob dies. Pet will generally have at least 80% health and be 100% long before I'm at full mana again.</P><P>It's getting harder and harder to find whites and yellows in Overthere, but the only thing I add on those is a second DOT. In those cases, my method is:</P><P><ul><li>Dooming Darkness</li><li>Fear</li><li>Pet</li><li>Scourge</li><li>Venom of the Snake (Dots in that order since scourge needs longer to work)</li><li>Call of Bones</li><li>Re-Fear when it breaks</li><li>Tap if it's taking too long and I think I'm going to have to Fear a third time.</li></ul></P><P>One last tip - it's better in general to pull the mobs that will run at the end of the battle (Sarnaks, Gnolls, Succulents, Bears) than mobs that fight to the bitter end (Cats, Skeletons, Rhinos). This saves you a bit of mana since if fear breaks near the end, the pet can take a beating for a little bit until the mob starts running.</P><P>Hope this helps!</P><P>Bene Moriore!</P><P><BR>Edited by - Ynar on 06/06/2002  10:57:18<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
