         How I Fear Kite Hill Giants in Rathe Mountians:</P><P>Make Pet<BR>Med to full<BR>Park pet at NW corner of Hill Giant Valley (best pathing for fear i think)<BR>DMF<BR>Aug pet<BR>Call of Bones</P><P>Go pull with Vampiric Embrace<BR>Run back to pet<BR>Sick pet on Giant<BR>Darkness<BR>Invoke Fear<BR>Run over to the little lump in the Fear Path<BR>Recast Invoke Fear (don't always have to do this)<BR>Loot</P><P>Immedialty pull again!!!</P><P>With Int of 202 and 300 extra mana items<BR>I can go through 8 Hill Giants (or so) before my health and mana get near 40%.</P><P>Then i med to full and do it again</P><P>Only time this stinks is during peak times when more than 10 people are there.  Also I HATE it when that lvl 55+ druid has all the Giants Root/Rotted at the top of the hill.</P><P>Gadol<BR>45 Necromancer<BR>Quellious Server</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
